CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- Hornets forward Michael Kidd-Gilchrist returned to the starting lineup Friday night for Charlotte's game against the Atlanta Hawks. Kidd-Gilchrist missed the last two games with a rib injury. The No. 2 overall pick in the 2013 draft was off to a solid start, averaging 11.3 points and 7.7 rebounds in his first three games for the Hornets (2-3).